\title{CausalCompetingRisks: Separable Effects for Causal Inference with Competing Events}
\description{
Discrete-time pooled logistic regression estimators for total, direct, and separable effects in survival analysis with competing events. Implements the g-formula and inverse probability weighting (IPW) methods from Stensrud et al. (2020) \doi{10.1080/01621459.2020.1765783} and Stensrud et al. (2021) \doi{10.1007/s10985-021-09530-8}. Provides cumulative incidence estimation, causal contrasts (risk differences and risk ratios), bootstrap confidence intervals, and diagnostic tools for assessing the isolation conditions underlying separable effects.
}
